	(gr_text "Decisions:\nDimensions: 145mm x 44mm\nUse Coplanar Waveguide for RF filter section for more confined EM fields \nUse 0.6x0.3 vias\nUse 7mil trace for CPW section with 4mil gap to coplanar ground (Standard PCB manufacturer limit) assuming 1ounce copper, 0.1mm high prepreg, 4.6 dielectric constant\nUse 1mm via distance (2xgap)\nUse 2mm between vias horizontally\nUse 7mil for microstrip for around 50ohm impedance\nfor microstrip with solid groundplane in layers 2,3 oriented horizontally for EM fields\nUse 0.4mm silkscreen width/height to balance readability/placement\nEnsure RF Mixer (U12) is far away from sensitive RF/analog front end"
